15.16	Barium_titanate	Barium titanate	Barium titanate is the inorganic compound with the chemical formula BaTiO3. Barium titanate is a white powder and transparent as larger crystals. This titanate is a ferroelectric ceramic material, with a photorefractive effect and piezoelectric properties.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9c/BaTiO3ceramics.JPG/200px-BaTiO3ceramics.JPG
